      <section id="lunch">
        <article class="card">
          <img src="veggieburger.jpg" alt="veggie burger" class="card-img">
          <h2>Lunch</h2>
          <p>Midday meals that nourish and inspire-lunch is the perfect pause where simple ingredients meet thoughtful preparation. Whether it's a hearty plate, a light bite, or something on-the-go, this collection celebrates the flavors that fuel your afternoon.</p>

          <h2>Veggie Burgers</h2>

          <h3>Prep:</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Serves: 4</li>
            <li>Prep Time: 15 mins</li>
            <li>Cooking Time: 15 mins</li>
            <li>Ready In: 30 mins</li>
          </ol>
          
          <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>2 c frozen edamame</li>
            <li>1 c coarsely chopped carrots</li>
            <li>1/3 c breadcrumbs</li>
            <li>1/4 c mayonnaise</li>
            <li>1 large clove garlic, chopped</li>
            <li>1/8 tsp chipotle chile powder</li>
            <li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>
            <li>4 hamburger buns</li>
          </ol>

          <h3>Directions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Combine edamame, carrots, and 1 tbsp water in medium microwave-safe bowl. Microwave covered at high until tender, about 5 minutes. Let stand 3 minutes; drain and cool slightly.</li>
            <li>Put edamame, carrots, breadcrumbes, mayonnaise, garlic, salt, and chipotle chili powder in food processor and process until uniformly ground, scraping down sides of bowl, if needed. Shape into 4 patties.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat and cook patties, turning once, until browned, about 8 minutes.</li>
            <li>Layer veggie burgers with your favorite burger toppings in buns.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>
          
      <section id="appetizers">
        <article class="card">
          <img src="grilled-shrimp-ceviche-00.jpg" alt="grilled shrimp ceviche" class="card-img">
          <h2>Appetizers</h2>
          <p>Kick off any gathering with small bites that bring big flavor. These appetizers are crafted to delight-whether you're hosting a casual get-together or setting the tone for a memorable meal. Perfectly portioned and beautifully styled, they offer a little taste of everything.</p>

          <h2>Grilled Shrimp Ceviche</h2>

          <h3>Prep</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Yields: 6 servings</li>
            <li>Prep Time: 30 mins</li>
            <li>Cook Time: 6 mins</li>
            <li>Total Time: 36 mins</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>For the marinated grilled shrimp:</li>
            <li>1/3 c vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1/2 large habanero pepper, seeded and minced</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tbsp brown sugar</li>
            <li>2 tsp smoked paprika</li>
            <li>1 tsp chili powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp garlic powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp onion powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp oregano</li>
            <li>1 tsp salt</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp black pepper</li>
            <li>1 lb raw jumbo shrimp, 16-20 per pound, peeled and deveined</li>
            <li>For the remainder of the ceviche:</li>
            <li>4 roma tomatoes, diced</li>
            <li>1 c fresh cilantro, chopped</li>
            <li>1/3 c diced red onion</li>
            <li>2 tsp minced jalapeno</li>
            <li>1 clove garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 large lime, juiced</li>
            <li>salt and pepper</li>
            <li>lime wedges for garnish</li>
            <li>tortilla chips, to serve</li>
          </ol>
          
        
          <h3>Directions:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>For the marinated grilled shrimp:</li>
            <li>In a small bowl with high sides, combine oil, habanero, garlic, brown sugar, smoked paprika, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, oregano, salt, and pepper. Use an immersion blender to completely process until there are no sizeable pieces. Place shrimp in a low, wide bowl and pour marinade over. Gently fold to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for 1-2 hours.</li>
            <li>Heat an outdoor grill to medium-high heat (about 475 degrees F). Clean and oil grill grates well. Set shrimp on grates. Grill for about 3 minutes per side, or until shrimp are no longer opaque and have a bit of char. Transfer to a plate to cool.</li>
            <li>To create the ceviche:</li>
            <li>In a medium bowl, fold together tomatoes, cilantro, red onion, jalapeno, garlic, and lime juice. Chop the grilled shrimp into 1/2 in or slightly smaller pieces and add to the bowl. Fold again. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed. Serve with extra lime wedges for squeezing over the top, plus tortilla chips for scooping.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="dinner">
        <article class="card">
          <img src="chicken-noodle-casserole.jpg" alt="chicken noodle casserole" class="card-img">
          <h2>Dinner</h2>
          <p>Evenings made easy-nourishing plates for busy hearts and hungry bellies.</p>

          <h2>Chicken Noodle Casserole</h2>

          <h3>Prep:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Prep Time: 10 mins</li>
            <li>Cook Time: 30 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 6</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>12 oz egg noodles uncooked</li>
            <li>4 c canned cooked chicken, chopped liquid saved and set to the side</li>
            <li>1 10 oz can cream of mushroom soup</li>
            <li>1 10 oz can cream of chicken soup</li>
            <li>1/2 c milk</li>
            <li>1 c shredded cheddar cheese</li>
            <li>2 c frozen peas</li>
            <li>8 oz mushrooms chopped</li>
            <li>1 4 oz can mushrooms, drained</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp garlic powder</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp onion powder</li>
            <li>salt and pepper to taste</li>
            <li>2 tbsp chopped parsley</li>
            <li>cooking spray</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Instructions:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Coat a 9"x13" pan with cooking spray.</li>
            <li>Cook the egg noodles according to package directions.</li>
            <li>In a large bowl combine the noodles, chicken, soup, milk, cheese, peas, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.</li>
            <li>Place the noodle mixture in the prepared baking dish and cover with foul. Bake for 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>
      
      <section id="sides">
        <article class="card">
          <img src="macandcheese.jpg" alt="macaroni and cheese" class="card-img">
          <h2>Sides</h2>
          <p>The perfect plus-one to any plate-flavorful sides that steal the spotlight.</p>

          <h2>Macaroni and Cheese</h2>

          <h3>Prep:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Serves: 4</li>
            <li>Prep Time: 20 mins</li>
            <li>Cooking Time: 30 mins</li>
            <li>Ready In: 50 mins</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>8 oz elbow macaroni</li>
            <li>1 can condensed cream of mushroom soup</li>
            <li>2 1/4 c cheddar cheese, divided</li>
            <li>3/4 c mayonnaise</li>
            <li>1/2 c 2% milk</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Directions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.</li>
            <li>Combine all ingredients except 1/2 c cheese in large bowl. Season, if desired with salt and pepper. Turn into 9 in baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 c cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="Dessert">
        <article class="card">
          <img src="bananacream.jpg" alt="banana cream pudding" class id="card-img">
          <h2>Dessert</h2>
          <p>Fancy fun wrapped up in one decadent delight</p>

          <h2>Banana Cream Pudding</h2>

          <h3>Prep:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Prep Time: 15 min</li>
            <li>Cook: 10 min</li>
            <li>Yield: 8</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Ingredients</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>1 qt milk</li>
            <li>2 c sugar, plus 1/4 c sugar</li>
            <li>8 large eggs, separated, whites stored for another use</li>
            <li>1 tsp banana extract</li>
            <li>1/3 c bourbon</li>
            <li>1/2 c cornstarch</li>
            <li>salt</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp vanilla extract, plus a splash</li>
            <li>2 tbsp butter, cut into cubes</li>
            <li>1 c heavy cream</li>
            <li>4 large bananas, sliced</li>
            <li>1 box vanilla wafers</li>
            <li>1/3 c creme de banana</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Directions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Scald milk, in a large sauce pot, with a pinch of sugar.</li>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, add egg yolks, banana extract, bourbon, and 2 c of sugar. Whish together until pale yellow and thickened. Add cornstarch and mix to combine. Very slowly, pour a little of the milk mixture. Once fully incorporated pour the entire mixture back into the pot and place over medium heat. Stir constantly until it comes to a simmer and the mixture thickens enough that it coats the back of a wooden spoon. Remove from heat and add a pinch of salt and vanilla extract, then add butter cubes and stir to make the mixture rich and super glossy.</li>
            <li>Transfer to a bowl and cover with plastic wrap, pressing the wrap onto the surface so it doesn't form a skin on the surface. Allow to cool.</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, using a hand mixer, whip the cream with 1/4 c of sugar and a splash of vanilla extract until you have stiff peaks. Set aside.</li>
            <li>slice bananas and add to pastry cream.</li>
            <li>Line a smal deep rectangular dish with vanilla wafers. Splash with creme de banana then cover with banana pastry cream. Top with whipped cream and refrigerate until ready to serve.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>   
